-- =============================================================================
-- LinkUp demo data — INSERT statements only (manual import; not run by app).
-- =============================================================================
-- Import (example):
--   mysql -h127.0.0.1 -P3307 -ulinkup_user -p linkup < scripts/seed-demo-data.sql
--
-- If FK errors on re-run, truncate child tables first or wrap your session with:
--   SET FOREIGN_KEY_CHECKS = 0;
--   ... your inserts ...
--   SET FOREIGN_KEY_CHECKS = 1;
--
-- Column names follow Spring Boot + Hibernate default (camelCase -> snake_case).
-- If `users` insert fails on the boolean column, run: SHOW CREATE TABLE users;
-- and rename `o_auth2_user` to match your DB (sometimes `oauth2_user` or `o_auth_2_user`).
--
-- Demo password for all rows below that set `password` (BCrypt, Spring Security):
--   Plain text: password
--   Hash verified by Spring Security unit test (BCryptPasswordEncoder.matches).
-- =============================================================================

